article.headline: Green Bay 70, N. Michigan 64
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Troy Cotton and Rahmon Fletcher scored 19 points apiece to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay to a 70-64 victory over Northern Michigan Wednesday night. The pair accounted for all seven of Green Bay's 3-pointers in the game, with Cotton making five. Randy Berry hit all five of his shots from the field and finished with 12 points for the Phoenix (4-1). Northern Michigan (0-2) shot 51 percent from the field and led by eight early in the second half. Marc Renelique had a game-high 23 points and eight rebounds for the Wildcats, making 7 of 10 from 3-point range. Raymont McElroy scored 16 and matched Renelique's eight rebounds, and led all players with five assists.
